&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Paper currency&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Only paper currency&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;coins &lt;/strong&gt;form the legal tender in India.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Non-Legal Tender-Money:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It is a&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;form of&amp;nbsp;money,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;which is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;generally accepted,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;but&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;legally is not bound to accept it&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Such as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cheques, bank drafts, bills of exchange,&amp;nbsp; postal orders, etc&lt;/span&gt;. are&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;not legal tenders&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;accepted only at the option of the&amp;nbsp;creditor, lender, or seller.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;also called optional money&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;because it&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;does not&amp;nbsp;have legal backing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and their&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;acceptance is&amp;nbsp;optional.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gold&lt;/strong&gt; can be exchanged as per understanding&amp;nbsp;between two parties, but it is&lt;strong&gt; not considered&amp;nbsp;a legal tender&lt;/strong&gt; in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Legal tender&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Limited Legal Tender Money: &lt;/strong&gt;This is&amp;nbsp;a form of money, which can be&lt;strong&gt; paid in&amp;nbsp;discharge of debt up to a certain limit,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and &lt;strong&gt;beyond&lt;/strong&gt; this limit, a&lt;strong&gt; person&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;may&amp;nbsp;refuse to accept the payment &lt;/strong&gt;and no&amp;nbsp;legal action can be taken against it.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coins&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;are&lt;strong&gt; limited legal tender &lt;/strong&gt;in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unlimited Legal Tender Money: &lt;/strong&gt;In&amp;nbsp;this form of money, which can be&lt;strong&gt; paid&amp;nbsp;in discharge of a debt of any amount&lt;/strong&gt;.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;person who refuses to accept this money legal action can be taken against.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paper notes/currency&lt;/strong&gt; are &lt;strong&gt;unlimited legal&amp;nbsp;tender&lt;/strong&gt; in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;Legal tender&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rsquo; is the money that is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;recognized by the law of the land, &lt;/strong&gt;as valid&amp;nbsp;for payment of debt.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;It must be&lt;strong&gt; accepted&amp;nbsp;for discharge of debt.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Th&lt;strong&gt;e RBI Act of 1934,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;which gives the&lt;strong&gt; Central Bank&lt;/strong&gt; the &lt;strong&gt;sole right&amp;nbsp;to issue banknotes&lt;/strong&gt;, states that &amp;ldquo;Every banknote&amp;nbsp;shall be legal tender at any place in&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India in payment for the amount expressed&amp;nbsp;therein&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The recognition or cancellation of the&amp;nbsp;legal tender status is important because&amp;nbsp;paper money derives all its value from the&amp;nbsp;Government&amp;rsquo;s recognition of it.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Also, for&amp;nbsp;a piece of paper to function as a: medium&amp;nbsp;of exchange and store of value, it needs to&amp;nbsp;enjoy unquestioning acceptance from the&amp;nbsp;public.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This can only be ensured by declaring&amp;nbsp;such paper currency notes as &amp;lsquo;legal tender&amp;nbsp;through a&amp;nbsp;fiat, with the RBI or the Centre&amp;nbsp;promising to &amp;lsquo;pay the bearer&amp;rsquo; an equivalent&amp;nbsp;sum if the currency note is presented to&amp;nbsp;them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Shark&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;a cold-blooded animal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The animals which cannot regulate their body temperature, are termed as cold-blooded animals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The body temperature of these animals fluctuates according to the temperature of the surroundings.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fishes, amphibians, and reptiles are cold-blooded animals&lt;/strong&gt;. Since shark is a fish, it is a cold-blooded animal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mammals and birds are warm-blooded animals.&lt;/strong&gt; Hence rest of the animals given in options are warm-blooded, their body temperature does not change with the temperature of the surroundings.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A whale is a warm-blooded animal as it is an aquatic mammal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No temple has been unearthed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The people of this civilization had a &lt;strong&gt;rich culture and complex social and religious systems&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;However, much about their religious beliefs and practices remains a &lt;strong&gt;mystery due to the lack of decipherable written records&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Archaeological evidence suggests that the &lt;strong&gt;Harappans may have worshipped a variety of deities, as indicated by the numerous figurines and seals discovered at various site&lt;/strong&gt;s. These include depictions of what appear to be goddess figures, often referred to as the &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Mother Goddess&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; and a figure in a yogic posture, often referred to as &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Pashupati&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;proto-Shiva&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Despite these findings,&lt;strong&gt; no specific structures identifiable as temples have been unearthed in any of the major Harappan sites&lt;/strong&gt;. This suggests that formal places of worship, as we understand them today, may not have been a part of Harappan religious practice.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It&amp;#39;s possible that &lt;strong&gt;religious rituals were conducted in homes or in public spaces, or that certain buildings&lt;/strong&gt; served multiple purposes, including religious functions. However, without definitive evidence, these remain theories.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, based on current archaeological findings and historical records, it is accurate to say that no temple has been unearthed from the Harappan civilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;About Indus valley Civilization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Script and Language&lt;/strong&gt;: The Harappan script is yet to be deciphered. Over 400 distinct Indus symbols have been found on seals, small tablets, ceramic pots and more than a dozen other materials. Despite many attempts, the &amp;#39;script&amp;#39; has not yet been deciphered and hence, much of Harappan life remains a mystery.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Art and Craft&lt;/strong&gt;: The Harappans were skilled craftsmen. They made beautiful pottery, seals, beads, and ornaments. The pottery was often decorated with geometric and animal designs. The seals, usually made of steatite, depicted a variety of animals and mythical beings and were likely used for trade.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trade and Commerce&lt;/strong&gt;: The Harappans engaged in trade with their neighbors in the Persian Gulf and Mesopotamia. Many Indus seals and a piece of Indus pottery have been discovered at ancient city sites in Mesopotamia.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decline of the Civilization&lt;/strong&gt;: The reasons for the decline of the Indus Valley Civilization are not clear. It&amp;#39;s believed that a combination of factors including climate change, tectonic events, or a change in river patterns could have contributed to its decline. There&amp;#39;s also a theory about an Aryan invasion, but it&amp;#39;s a subject of ongoing debate among scholars.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rediscovery&lt;/strong&gt;: The ruins of the Indus Valley Civilization were first discovered in the 1920s by a railway engineer named R. D. Banerji. Two of the main sites, Harappa and Mohenjo-Daro, have since been extensively excavated.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Legacy&lt;/strong&gt;: The civilization&amp;#39;s sophisticated urban planning, architecture, and drainage systems indicate a highly organized society. Some of its practices, such as the cultivation of cotton and rice, have had a lasting impact and continue to be important in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;International trade:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;International trade is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;exchange of goods and services&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;among countries across national boundaries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Countries need to trade to obtain commodities, they cannot produce themselves or they can purchase elsewhere at a lower price.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;International trade is the result of specialisation in production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trade barriers:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A trade barrier is a government or public-sector measure, that makes imported goods and services less competitive than locally produced goods and services.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;set of barriers&lt;/strong&gt; erected by the government in order &lt;strong&gt;to restrict free trade&lt;/strong&gt; between national economies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are three major trade barriers - natural barriers, tariff barriers, and&amp;nbsp;nontariff barriers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Protectionism:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Protectionism is a term used to describe &lt;strong&gt;government policies that limit foreign trade in order to benefit home businesses.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For the sake of a &lt;strong&gt;domestic economy, protectionist policies impose certain limits on world trade.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Protectionist policies are often implemented to boost economic activity, but they can also be prompted by safety or quality concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tariffs, import quotas, product standards, and subsidies &lt;/strong&gt;are some of the most &lt;strong&gt;common policy &lt;/strong&gt;measures used by governments to implement &lt;strong&gt;protectionist policies.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Supporters of protectionism claim that the measures can help, create jobs at home, boost GDP, and make a country&amp;#39;s economy more globally competitive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Thus, t&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;he use of trade barriers to protect a nation&amp;rsquo;s industries from foreign competition is called p&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;rotectionism.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free Trade:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The act of &lt;strong&gt;opening up economies for trading&lt;/strong&gt; is known as free trade or trade liberalisation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is done by bringing down trade barriers like tariffs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Free trade allows goods and services from everywhere to compete with domestic products and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Balance of Trade:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Balance of trade records the &lt;strong&gt;volume of goods and services&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;imported as well as exported by a country to other countries.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If the value of imports is more than the value of a country&amp;rsquo;s exports, the country has a negative or unfavourable balance of trade.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If the value of exports is more than the value of imports, then the country has a positive or favourable balance of trade.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quota:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A quota is a &lt;strong&gt;government-imposed trade&lt;/strong&gt; restriction that &lt;strong&gt;restricts the number or monetary worth of commodities a country&lt;/strong&gt; can import or export in a given period.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In international trade, countries utilise quotas to help regulate the volume of trade between them and other countries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The President of the Indian National Congress at the time of the Quit India Movement was&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maulana Abul Kalam Azad.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Quit India Movement, also known as the August Movement, was a mass civil disobedience movement &lt;/strong&gt;launched by Mahatma Gandhi o&lt;strong&gt;n August 8, 1942,&lt;/strong&gt; demanding the withdrawal of the British from India.&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maulana Abul Kalam Azad was a prominent Indian freedom fighter, a close associate of Mahatma Gandhi,&lt;/strong&gt; and the first Education Minister of independent India.&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The president of the Indian National Congress at the time of the Quit India Movement was&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Maulana Abul Kalam Azad.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;He was elected twice as the president, first in 1923 and the second time in 1940.&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;He served as the&lt;strong&gt; President of the Indian National Congress from 1940 to 1945.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;Under his leadership, Congress played an active role in the Quit India Movement and other mass agitations against British rule.&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;Azad was a strong &lt;strong&gt;advocate of Hindu-Muslim unity and worked towards promoting communal harmony in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;He was a prominent leader in the freedom struggle and a scholar of Islam.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;The Quit India Movement was launched&amp;nbsp;on 8th August 1942.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was launched at the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Bombay session&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the All India Congress Committee by Mahatma Gandhi, during&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;World War II,&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;demanding an end to British rule in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The movement is also known as&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;August Kranti&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Gowalia Tank Maidan,&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the place from where it was launched is&amp;nbsp;known as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;August Kranti Maidan.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The slogan was&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Do or Die&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;given by Gandhiji and&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Quit India&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On the next day,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;all major Congress leaders&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;Gandhi, Nehru, Patel, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;were&amp;nbsp;arrested.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Singapore.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);   &quot;&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);   &quot;&gt;Singapore&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);   &quot;&gt;, on 4 July &lt;strong&gt;1943&lt;/strong&gt;, Subhash Chandra Bose was elected as the president of the&lt;strong&gt; Indian Independence League&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);   &quot;&gt;Rasbihari Bose voluntarily retired and appointed him as the &lt;strong&gt;head of the Indian National Army.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rash Behari Bose&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;chaired the&lt;strong&gt; Indian Independence League&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;1942&lt;/strong&gt; to formally launch the Indian National Army.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;The idea of the Indian National Army (INA) was first conceived in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Malaya&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Mohan Singh&lt;/span&gt;, an Indian officer of the British Indian Army.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;In&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;March 1942&lt;/span&gt;, a conference of India was held in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Tokyo&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Indian Independence League&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;was formed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;At &lt;strong&gt;Bangkok&lt;/strong&gt; Conference,&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Rash Behari Bose&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;was elected as President of the League.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;In Singapore, he was assisted by Rash Behari Bose.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;In October 1943, he set up a provisional Indian Government with headquarters at Rangoon and Singapore.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;INA annexed&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Andaman and Nicobar&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;with &lt;strong&gt;Japanese&lt;/strong&gt; help and named them&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Shaheed and Swaraj&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(30, 43, 51);    user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;About Indian Independence League:&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p class=&quot;_2tazz&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: -0.36px; overflow: auto hidden; user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Indian Independence League&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;was a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Political Organization&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;that was founded by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Rash Behari Bose in&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; letter-spacing: -0.36px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;1920-1940&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p class=&quot;_2tazz&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: -0.36px; overflow: auto hidden; user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;It was set up to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;organize those Living outside India into seeking the removal of East India&amp;#39;s colonial rule over India&lt;/span&gt;. After the arrival of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Subhas Chandra Bose in South East Asia&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;revamp&amp;nbsp;of the Indian National Army&lt;/span&gt;, and after coming into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;South East Asia the League came under his leadership.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p class=&quot;_2tazz&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: -0.36px; overflow: auto hidden; user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;He was born on&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;25th May 1886 in Bardhaman, West Bengal&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;Ras Behari Bose&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;was one of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;main organizers of the Ghadar Party in 1913.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p class=&quot;_2tazz&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: -0.36px; overflow: auto hidden; user-select: initial !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;user-select: initial !important; font-weight: bolder;  line-height: 20px;&quot;&gt;He handed over the Indian National Army to Subhash Chandra Bose in Singapore in 1940.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
